CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 16, 1961, pg. A31 reads: " Nine-Year Veteran - Bob French, a nine-year veteran with Seagram Distillers, invites you to use Seagram's products for your holiday entertaining or personal enjoyment. Seagram Seven Crown is the nation's top-selling whiskey, with Seagram VO running a close second.  In addition, Seagram Extra Dry Gin is pulling fast (Adv.) - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Sales Representative Robert "Bob" P. French Jr. standing behind display of Seagram products in interior with hourglass and diamond patterned curtains
